5-7 East 93rd Street, north side, east of Fifth Avenue.
About 1912.
Fifth Avenue at S.E. corner of 93rd Street. June 1925.  Neg. # 1049

Fifth Avenue at N. E. corner of 93rd Street, across clearing at S. E. corner.
About 1925.

(1)
Tompkins Square: A northeastward view across the northeasterly corner of same, showing the wading pool in the central-easterly half. Buildings shown face on the east side of Ave. B, north from East 9th (right) to 10th (left) Streets, prominent of which is the Christodoro House at the N.E. corner of the first two points.

August 31, 1928.

P. L. Sperr.

(2 & 3)
A set of 2 views of the same pool. No. 2 is due east to Ave. B at East 8th Street and showing St. Brigid's Roman Catholic Church at the S.E. corner of same. No. 3 is in the opposite direction, westward to Ave. A.

July 24, 1930.

P. L. Sperr.

April 14th, 1940

P.L.Sperr,

East 93rd Street, at, adjoining and east of the S.E. corner of Fifth Ave (background to foreground). The private houses bear Nos. 4, 6 and 8 while the apartment house at the corner is No. 1116 Fifth Ave. Note a portion of Central Park in the background.

June 22, 1936.

W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.
